Request-Response Cycle
Client sends a request.
Server receives and processes it.
Server may interact with a database or other services.
Server sends a response with a status code and data.
Client displays or uses the response.
Key Differences
GET vs POST
GET retrieves data.
POST creates data.
PUT vs PATCH
PUT replaces the entire resource.
PATCH updates only specified fields.
401 vs 403
401 Unauthorized: User is not authenticated (not logged in or invalid credentials).
403 Forbidden: User is authenticated but doesn't have permission.
