REST (Representational State Transfer)
Definition
REST is an architectural style for designing web APIs. It provides a standard way to organize endpoints so that APIs are simple, consistent, and scalable.
Key idea: The URL represents the resource, and the HTTP method represents the action.
Resource
A resource is the object your API manages.
Examples:
Users
Products
Books
Students
Orders
REST endpoints use plural nouns.
/users
/products
/books
/orders
