Path Parameters
Used to identify a specific resource.
Example:
/users/15
15 is the user ID.
Query Parameters
Used to filter, search, sort, or paginate results.
Examples:
/users?page=2
/products?category=laptop
/rooms?city=Kuwait&price=500
JSON Response Format
A REST API usually returns JSON.
Success:
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "User fetched successfully",
  "data": {
    "id": 10,
    "name": "Kash"
  }
}
Error:
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "User not found"
}
API Versioning
To avoid breaking older applications, APIs are versioned.
Example:
/api/v1/users
/api/v2/users
Older clients continue using v1 while newer clients can use v2.
REST Best Practices
✅ Use nouns, not verbs.
Correct:
/users
/orders
Incorrect:
/getUsers
/createOrder
✅ Use plural resource names.
/users
/products
✅ Keep URLs lowercase.
Correct:
/products
Incorrect:
/Products
✅ Use the correct HTTP status codes (200, 201, 204, 400, 404, etc.).
